ol.li:
Modify the environment.json file to configure the VLANs and network
          addresses as appropriate for your environment. Set the following for the CLM, CAN, and BLS
          network:"cidr": 
"start-address":  The three controller nodes
          should have CLM, CAN, EXT, BLS on eth0 and TUL on eth1. 


            Example:

{
    "product": {
        "version": 1
    },

    "node-type": [
        {
            "name": "CCN",
            "interface-map": [
                {
                    "name": "INTF0",
                    "ethernet-port-map": {
                        "interface-ports": [ "eth0" ]
                    },
                    "logical-network-map": [
                        {
                            "name": "CLM",
                            "type": "vlan",
                            "segment-id": "502",
                            "network-address": {
                                "cidr": "10.50.2.0/24",
                                "start-address": "10.50.2.10",
                                "gateway": "10.50.2.1"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "CAN",
                            "type": "vlan",
                            "segment-id": "504",
                            "network-address": {
                                "cidr": "10.50.4.0/24",
                                "start-address": "10.50.4.10"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "BLS",
                            "type": "vlan",
                            "segment-id": "76",
                            "network-address": {
                                "cidr": "172.16.76.0/19",
                                "start-address": "172.16.76.10"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}
            NOTE: The Helion Configuration Processor assigns the first address of the CLM
            address range to itself for serving python and debian repositories. Make sure that you
            set the first IP address of the CLM range for the eth2 (CLM) address of the HLM
            node.

Modify the definition.json file: 

Set the number of compute systems to 2.
              "count": 2, //number of computes in the resource pool

Update the ansible-vars section with all the information based on
              your setup.

Make sure you have two NTP entries in the upstream_ntp_servers
              fields in the definition.json file as seen in the following example.
              If you have only one NTP server in your environment, specify the same NTP server
              twice. Example:
              {
    "product": {
      "version": 1
      },

    "cloud": {
      "name": "b44tb4",
      "nickname": "b44tb4",
      "server-config": "nodes.json",
      "environment": "environment.json",
      "network-config": ".hos/lnet-control-data.json"
    },

    "failure-zones": [
      {
        "name": "fz1"
      },
      {
        "name": "fz2"
      },
      {
        "name": "fz3"
      }
    ],

    "control-planes": [
      {
        "file": ".hos/ccp-1x3-ss.json",
        "resource-nodes": []
      }
    ],

    "ansible-vars": {
      "dns_address": "10.1.2.44",
      "dns_domain_name": "helion.cg",
      "ldap_url": "10.1.2.44",
